@page "/ControlSamples/PageStyleSheet"

<PageTitle>PageStyleSheet - Dynamic CSS Loading</PageTitle>

@* Load page-specific CSS dynamically *@
<PageStyleSheet Href="css/PageStyleSheetDemo.css" />

<h2>PageStyleSheet</h2>

<p>
    <code>PageStyleSheet</code> dynamically loads CSS stylesheets when a component renders
    and removes them when the component disposes. This is the Blazor equivalent of Web Forms'
    pattern for page-specific CSS via <code>ContentPlaceHolder</code>.
</p>

@* ─────────────── Visual indicator that CSS is loaded ─────────────── *@

<div class="pss-demo-banner">
    <span>
        <strong>CSS Loaded!</strong> The purple styling you see comes from 
        <code>PageStyleSheetDemo.css</code>, which was loaded by <code>PageStyleSheet</code>.
    </span>
</div>

@* ─────────────── Section 1: Basic Usage ─────────────── *@

<div class="pss-demo-container">
    <h3>1. Basic Usage</h3>
    <p>Simply add a <code>PageStyleSheet</code> component pointing to your CSS file:</p>
    
    <pre><code>&lt;PageStyleSheet Href="css/PageStyleSheetDemo.css" /&gt;</code></pre>
    
    <p>
        The CSS is loaded when this page renders and <strong>unloaded when you navigate away</strong>.
        Try it — click a link in the navigation, then use your browser's back button to return.
    </p>
</div>

@* ─────────────── Section 2: Navigation Test ─────────────── *@

<div class="pss-demo-container">
    <h3>2. Test Navigation Behavior</h3>
    
    <div class="pss-nav-test">
        <p>Navigate away and come back to see the CSS load/unload:</p>
        <p>
            <a href="/">← Go to Home</a> &nbsp;|&nbsp; 
            <a href="/ControlSamples/Button">Go to Button →</a>
        </p>
        <p><small>When you return, the purple styling reappears because PageStyleSheet reloads the CSS.</small></p>
    </div>
</div>

@* ─────────────── Section 3: Why HeadContent Doesn't Work ─────────────── *@

<div class="pss-demo-container">
    <h3>3. Why Not HeadContent?</h3>
    
    <p>
        Blazor's built-in <code>HeadContent</code> component seems like it should work, but it has limitations:
    </p>
    
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Layout limitation:</strong> <code>HeadContent</code> only works in page components, not layouts</li>
        <li><strong>No cleanup:</strong> CSS added via <code>HeadContent</code> persists after navigation</li>
        <li><strong>Static SSR issues:</strong> Different behavior between static and interactive modes</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p>
        <code>PageStyleSheet</code> solves all of these by using JavaScript interop with a 
        reference-counting registry that properly manages the stylesheet lifecycle.
    </p>
    
    <pre><code>// HeadContent — doesn't work in layouts, no cleanup
&lt;HeadContent&gt;
    &lt;link href="page.css" rel="stylesheet" /&gt;
&lt;/HeadContent&gt;

// PageStyleSheet — works anywhere, cleans up on dispose
&lt;PageStyleSheet Href="page.css" /&gt;</code></pre>
</div>

@* ─────────────── Section 4: Web Forms Migration ─────────────── *@

<div class="pss-demo-container">
    <h3>4. Migration from Web Forms</h3>
    
    <h4>Before (Web Forms)</h4>
    <pre><code>&lt;%@@ Page ... MasterPageFile="~/Site.Master" %&gt;

&lt;asp:Content ContentPlaceHolderID="head" runat="server"&gt;
    &lt;link href="CSS/Products.css" rel="stylesheet" /&gt;
&lt;/asp:Content&gt;

&lt;asp:Content ContentPlaceHolderID="MainContent" runat="server"&gt;
    &lt;!-- Page content --&gt;
&lt;/asp:Content&gt;</code></pre>
    
    <h4>After (Blazor)</h4>
    <pre><code>@@page "/products"

&lt;PageStyleSheet Href="CSS/Products.css" /&gt;

&lt;!-- Page content --&gt;</code></pre>
    
    <p>
        The migration is straightforward: replace the <code>ContentPlaceHolder</code> pattern
        with a single <code>PageStyleSheet</code> component at the top of your page.
    </p>
</div>

@* ─────────────── Section 5: Advanced Options ─────────────── *@

<div class="pss-demo-container">
    <h3>5. Advanced Options</h3>
    
    <p><code>PageStyleSheet</code> supports additional attributes for specialized scenarios:</p>
    
    <table class="table">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Parameter</th>
                <th>Description</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td><code>Href</code></td>
                <td>Required. URL of the stylesheet (relative or absolute)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><code>Media</code></td>
                <td>Media query (e.g., <code>"print"</code>, <code>"(max-width: 600px)"</code>)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><code>Id</code></td>
                <td>Optional ID for the link element</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><code>Integrity</code></td>
                <td>SRI hash for CDN resources</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><code>CrossOrigin</code></td>
                <td>Cross-origin setting (typically <code>"anonymous"</code> with Integrity)</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
    
    <pre><code>@@* Print-only stylesheet *@@
&lt;PageStyleSheet Href="css/print.css" Media="print" /&gt;

@@* CDN resource with SRI *@@
&lt;PageStyleSheet Href="https://cdn.example.com/styles.css" 
                Integrity="sha384-abc123..." 
                CrossOrigin="anonymous" /&gt;</code></pre>
</div>

@* ─────────────── Section 6: Render Mode Behavior ─────────────── *@

<div class="pss-demo-container">
    <h3>6. Render Mode Behavior</h3>
    
    <p><code>PageStyleSheet</code> adapts to different Blazor render modes:</p>
    
    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>Static SSR:</strong> Renders a <code>&lt;link&gt;</code> tag directly into HTML.
            No unload on navigation (full page reload clears it).
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Prerendering + Interactive:</strong> Renders static <code>&lt;link&gt;</code> during
            prerender, then JavaScript takes over after hydration.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>InteractiveServer / WebAssembly:</strong> Full lifecycle management — CSS loads
            on render and unloads on dispose (navigation away).
        </li>
    </ul>
    
    <p>
        This page demonstrates the full load/unload behavior. Navigate away and back to see it in action.
    </p>
</div>

@* ─────────────── Section 7: Layout CSS ─────────────── *@

<div class="pss-demo-container">
    <h3>7. Using PageStyleSheet in Layouts</h3>
    
    <p>
        You can also use <code>PageStyleSheet</code> in your layout file for CSS that should
        persist across all pages:
    </p>
    
    <pre><code>@@* MainLayout.razor *@@
@@inherits LayoutComponentBase

@@* Layout-wide CSS — persists as long as layout is rendered *@@
&lt;PageStyleSheet Href="css/layout-theme.css" /&gt;

&lt;div class="layout-wrapper"&gt;
    @@Body
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
    
    <p>
        Since the layout component stays alive across navigations, its CSS persists.
        Page-specific CSS (like on this page) loads and unloads as pages change.
    </p>
</div>

<hr />

